Interview Strategy & Tips 
• Think out loud — interviewers want to see your problem-solving process, not just the answer 
• If stuck, start with brute force, then optimize — show your thinking evolution 
• Ask clarifying questions before coding — scope, edge cases, constraints 
• Write clean, readable code — comments where needed, meaningful variable names 
• For system design questions, think: Scale → Availability → Consistency → Components 
• Always test your code mentally with edge cases: empty array, null, 0, negative numbers 
• Know Big O notation basics — O(1), O(n), O(n²), O(log n) — interviewers often ask 
• For behavioral questions, prepare 3-4 STAR stories from your projects 
• Have questions ready for the interviewer — shows genuine interest 
• Follow up via email within 24 hours thanking them for the opportunity 
